OL,5, Fifteen years of wage stagnation has   
OL,6, left British workers #11,000 worse off 
OL,7, per year, according to research shared 
OL,8, exclusively with BBC Panorama.         
OL,10,FThe figures come from the Resolution   
OL,11,FFoundation think tank, which focuses on
OL,12,Flow-to-middle income households.       
OL,14,FIt also found typical UK household     
OL,15,Fincomes have fallen further behind     
OL,16,Fthose in Germany. In 2008, the gap was 
OL,17,Fover #500 a year, now it is #4,000.    
OL,19,FThe Treasury says the UK economy is    
OL,20,Fmore resilient than many predicted.    
